  "title": "RESTAURANT CAPTAIN",
  "description": "<p>The captain also takes initial beverage and food orders, delivering cocktails, beer and other beverages to the guests at the table. In the absence of a sommelier or wine steward, your job is to recommend particular pairings for specific food items and then decant bottles and serve the wine. This requires a complete knowledge of all of the items on the menu and any special items in order to help guests make their choices for the meal..</p><p>JOB REQUIRMENTS</p><p>Always greet and welcome guests promptly in a warm and friendly manner.</p><p>Always thank and give fond farewell to guests conveying anticipation for their next visit.</p><p>Assist guest with table reservation.</p><p>Assist guest while seating.</p><p>Ensure guest are serviced within specified time.</p><p>Has a good knowledge of menu and presentation standards.</p><p>Speak with guests and staff using clear and professional language, and answer phone calls using appropriate telephone etiquette.</p><p>Restaurant Captain Duties and Responsibilities:</p><p>•\tAlways greet and welcome guests promptly in a warm and friendly manner.</p><p>•\tAlways thank and give fond farewell to guests conveying anticipation for their next visit.</p><p>•\tAssist guests with table reservations.</p><p>•\tAssist guests while seating.</p><p>•\tEnsure guests are serviced within the specified time.</p><p>•\tHas a good knowledge of menu and presentation standards.</p><p>•\tSpeak with guests and staff using clear and professional language, and answer phone calls using appropriate telephone etiquette.</p><p>•\tAble to answer any questions regarding the menu and assist with menu selections.</p><p>•\tAble to anticipate any unexpected guest need and react promptly and tactfully.</p><p>•\tAlways applies service techniques correctly at all times, and serves Food & Beverage items with enthusiasm.</p><p>•\tServe food courses and  beverages to guests.</p><p>•\tSet tables according to the type of event and service standards.</p><p>•\tRecord transactions/orders in Point of Sales systems at the time of order.</p><p>•\tCommunicate with the kitchen regarding any menu questions, the length of wait, and product availability.</p><p>•\tCommunicate additional meal requirements, allergies, dietary needs, and special requests to the kitchen.</p><p>•\tCheck with guests to ensure satisfaction with each food course and beverage.</p><p>•\tResponsible for clearing, collecting, and returning food and beverage items to the proper area.</p><p>•\tMaintain cleanliness of work areas, china, glass, etc. throughout the shift.</p><p>•\tReviews order dockets ensuring accurate and timely preparations for order requirements accordingly.</p><p></p>",
